entertain the visi- tors. The young people were in one of the inner rooms, not considering it necessary to take part in receiving the visitors. The count met the guests and saw them off, inviting them all to dinner. 
"I am very, very grateful to you, mon cher" or "ma chre" he called everyone without excep- tion and without the slightest variation in his tone, "my dear," whether they were above or below him in rank "I thank you for myself and for our two dear ones whose name day we are keeping.
